WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.480
The general environment in which I evolve is

2
00:00:05.480 --> 00:00:07.260
the engine that can develop me.

3
00:00:07.860 --> 00:00:11.620
If I take a seed and put it in the fridge, not much will happen.

4
00:00:11.840 --> 00:00:16.340
If I put it in the earth, there is light, sun, heat, it can develop.

5
00:00:16.640 --> 00:00:21.660
If you are in a complicated emotional or other environment, it will

6
00:00:21.660 --> 00:00:22.100
influence.

7
00:00:22.440 --> 00:00:27.300
We know more and more that we can talk about the genetic egg and more and more that we talk about epigenetics.

8
00:00:28.072 --> 00:00:34.972
the force of the environment represents almost 90% of

9
00:00:34.972 --> 00:00:36.212
this power.

10
00:00:36.472 --> 00:00:41.252
The question arises as to what environment your patient lives in.

11
00:00:43.452 --> 00:00:48.152
I very often ask the question, where do you live, what do you experience,

12
00:00:48.272 --> 00:00:49.912
what have you experienced, what are...

13
00:00:49.912 --> 00:00:55.132
It's all this anamnesis side, but with the idea of, I take a kind of layer

14
00:00:55.132 --> 00:00:56.072
around and I see it.

15
00:00:56.144 --> 00:01:01.484
what's happening. We need an environment to develop

16
00:01:01.484 --> 00:01:02.704
and secondly

17
00:01:02.704 --> 00:01:08.004
space. To give space back to the mind, to give space back to the tissue,

18
00:01:08.664 --> 00:01:09.424
to give space back

19
00:01:09.424 --> 00:01:15.364
to an emotion. Embryology is functional anatomy. And

20
00:01:15.364 --> 00:01:16.404
what does that mean? It means

21
00:01:16.404 --> 00:01:21.864
that it is anatomy that is first in motion. Second, it

22
00:01:21.864 --> 00:01:23.204
is anatomy that uses

23
00:01:23.204 --> 00:01:24.144
the four years.

24
00:01:24.217 --> 00:01:28.697
five dimensions we know, up, down, left, etc. And the fourth dimension

25
00:01:28.697 --> 00:01:33.597
which is the notion of chronos, of time. You will have to be able to look at this

26
00:01:33.597 --> 00:01:38.917
little embryo developing through all its movements and also with sections. This

27
00:01:38.917 --> 00:01:42.857
notion is memory. This notion of time is also a notion of memory,

28
00:01:42.997 --> 00:01:48.117
that is to say that you carry time within you. You are a concentration

29
00:01:48.117 --> 00:01:49.397
 of time. And

30
00:01:49.397 --> 00:01:52.217
sometimes in the body there are specific areas.

31
00:01:52.949 --> 00:01:55.609
which are concentrated areas where the person is blocked.

32
00:01:56.949 --> 00:02:00.669
A word, a gesture, a look can block a person for their whole life.

33
00:02:02.589 --> 00:02:06.069
And sometimes, this time is found in the tissues.

34
00:02:07.029 --> 00:02:09.329
And sometimes, you can work, you've already noticed,

35
00:02:09.449 --> 00:02:10.809
you've done some work, and then all of a sudden,

36
00:02:10.869 --> 00:02:13.109
there's an emotional release that happens.

37
00:02:13.669 --> 00:02:16.069
You have, in fact, released a concentration.

38
00:02:17.949 --> 00:02:19.569
You put it back in its space.

39
00:02:20.361 --> 00:02:22.241
And that, in embryology, is important.

40
00:02:22.421 --> 00:02:24.121
Because we will be able to find these notions.

41
00:02:24.401 --> 00:02:26.741
If you remember the short film we saw this morning,

42
00:02:27.541 --> 00:02:30.221
you saw that there were movements where we moved forward,

43
00:02:30.461 --> 00:02:32.181
and then all of a sudden, movements where it moved back.

44
00:02:32.441 --> 00:02:34.201
Movements as if there was a wave, like that.

45
00:02:34.941 --> 00:02:37.301
But if you observe that, if there is a movement like that,

46
00:02:37.361 --> 00:02:38.361
it means there are points of support.

47
00:02:39.741 --> 00:02:44.461
And we will use them as therapeutic tools.

48
00:02:45.361 --> 00:02:47.041
Because the body knows these points of support.

49
00:02:47.161 --> 00:02:48.361
If you give them a good point of support,

50
00:02:49.054 --> 00:02:52.394
and it knows where it can develop, it can rebuild itself.

51
00:02:53.074 --> 00:02:57.814
There is the notion that you have time, that there are tissues, that there are fluids,

52
00:02:58.634 --> 00:03:00.454
and everything is expressed in a constellation,

53
00:03:00.714 --> 00:03:02.934
we say that mind, body, spirit are united.

54
00:03:03.114 --> 00:03:04.434
Mind, body, spirit.

55
00:03:05.694 --> 00:03:09.334
So osteopathy is a science based on the art of touch,

56
00:03:10.374 --> 00:03:12.754
which offers true knowledge of the living heart,

57
00:03:14.254 --> 00:03:16.334
the one that tells the story of anatomy,

58
00:03:16.506 --> 00:03:18.386
linked to the movement of spirit and mind.

59
00:03:19.226 --> 00:03:22.346
One of the goals of osteopathy is to improve exchanges

60
00:03:22.346 --> 00:03:25.226
and to have an impact down to the cellular level,

61
00:03:25.366 --> 00:03:27.566
and even, I think we go further,

62
00:03:27.706 --> 00:03:30.326
that we have impacts even on the genetic level.

63
00:03:30.586 --> 00:03:34.826
We now prove it by the phenomena of tensegrity

64
00:03:34.826 --> 00:03:39.166
and the phenomena of epigenetics,

65
00:03:39.346 --> 00:04:00.798
that in fact we have a very profound impact, and we will see how far it goes. The path... My professor, my teacher, had suggested to me, first told me that you must study embryology. He tells me that when you understand embryology well, you will understand what anatomy means. Anatomy will give you physiology. This physiology, you will also have to study its pathos. Its pathophysiology. Then we have psychology, then we have philosophy. Finally, there is spirituality. How conception develops, and where it is how I die. That death...

66
00:04:01.778 --> 00:04:02.498
Its pathophysiology.

67
00:04:03.498 --> 00:04:06.478
Then we have psychology, then we have philosophy.

68
00:04:06.778 --> 00:04:08.458
Finally, there is spirituality.

69
00:04:08.618 --> 00:04:11.638
How conception develops, and where it is how I die.

70
00:04:11.858 --> 00:04:12.578
That death...

71
00:04:13.151 --> 00:04:15.091
on a developmental level

72
00:04:15.091 --> 00:04:15.791
is useful.

73
00:04:15.971 --> 00:04:17.351
If there is no cellular death,

74
00:04:17.411 --> 00:04:18.311
I don't like the word death,

75
00:04:19.551 --> 00:04:22.191
I would always say transformation.

76
00:04:23.911 --> 00:04:25.771
It is a continuous transformation.

77
00:04:26.291 --> 00:04:27.871
This power that was already established

78
00:04:27.871 --> 00:04:29.271
in the first cell,

79
00:04:30.031 --> 00:04:32.231
It continues until the end of your life.

80
00:04:33.091 --> 00:04:35.471
Until your last breath.

81
00:04:36.831 --> 00:04:38.531
That is, you have this capacity

82
00:04:38.531 --> 00:04:40.611
to take the breath of life.

83
00:04:41.783 --> 00:04:43.023
the breath of life is there

84
00:04:43.023 --> 00:04:44.303
and then I breathe out

85
00:04:45.543 --> 00:04:46.283
and I still have

86
00:04:46.283 --> 00:04:48.243
the energy to

87
00:04:49.283 --> 00:04:50.303
take it again

88
00:04:50.303 --> 00:04:52.063
so I can still participate

89
00:04:52.063 --> 00:04:54.623
and we do that every time, that's where we have the transformation

90
00:04:54.623 --> 00:04:56.723
I think sometimes people

91
00:04:56.723 --> 00:04:57.783
they are stuck in time

92
00:04:58.343 --> 00:05:00.263
and that they sometimes come to get

93
00:05:00.703 --> 00:05:01.803
information about it

94
00:05:02.683 --> 00:05:04.843
very often people when they follow

95
00:05:04.843 --> 00:05:06.203
these courses, afterwards in practice

96
00:05:06.203 --> 00:05:07.563
something happens

97
00:05:07.563 --> 00:05:08.723
because

98
00:05:08.796 --> 00:05:12.176
we go into something where no mind can intervene,

99
00:05:12.356 --> 00:05:14.376
but there is a modification that happens inside.

100
00:05:14.836 --> 00:05:19.236
Because we will see the development of the perfect embryo, as they say.

101
00:05:19.336 --> 00:05:23.196
We will be in the blueprint, which keeps its median line, which has no deviation.

102
00:05:23.756 --> 00:05:27.176
This is my birth, this is the space of my conception.

103
00:05:28.476 --> 00:05:32.516
And sometimes you have the median line here, you are in the right axis.

104
00:05:33.476 --> 00:05:35.696
Sometimes you can already deviate at your conception.

105
00:05:36.868 --> 00:05:39.288
be deviated at your birth, you can be deviated by a trauma.

106
00:05:40.308 --> 00:05:41.348
And we must recognize

107
00:05:41.348 --> 00:05:42.168
these points.

108
00:05:43.208 --> 00:05:44.488
Non-recognition

109
00:05:46.128 --> 00:05:46.768
develops all

110
00:05:46.768 --> 00:05:49.148
compensatory activities.

111
00:05:49.508 --> 00:05:51.148
So I must, at some point,

112
00:05:51.908 --> 00:05:53.568
by the quality of my presence,

113
00:05:53.728 --> 00:05:54.728
by the quality of touch,

114
00:05:54.868 --> 00:05:56.888
by what the tissue will inform you,

115
00:05:58.528 --> 00:05:59.408
be able to recognize

116
00:05:59.408 --> 00:05:59.968
these spaces.

117
00:06:01.028 --> 00:06:03.048
And there, he can have

118
00:06:03.048 --> 00:06:03.588
a...

119
00:06:05.540 --> 00:06:06.300
a trust

120
00:06:07.600 --> 00:06:08.360
of correction

121
00:06:09.560 --> 00:06:11.100
you just have to be present

122
00:06:11.100 --> 00:06:11.800
for the touch

123
00:06:13.960 --> 00:06:15.180
because there is no will

124
00:06:15.180 --> 00:06:16.720
that's what's really important

125
00:06:16.720 --> 00:06:19.260
the body has a capacity for self-regulation

126
00:06:20.040 --> 00:06:20.920
of self-regulation

127
00:06:20.920 --> 00:06:22.680
and to maintain its health

128
00:06:23.320 --> 00:06:25.180
and so this notion of strength

129
00:06:25.180 --> 00:06:26.440
of nature

130
00:06:26.440 --> 00:06:28.300
is to reconnect with that

131
00:06:29.020 --> 00:06:29.980
we see very well

132
00:06:29.980 --> 00:06:32.860
if now there is no more human impact

133
00:06:33.013 --> 00:06:36.993
nature quickly reclaims its rights and we have been somewhat cut off from

134
00:06:36.993 --> 00:06:42.033
that. As long as this development is there, nature is there. The less we intervene, the better

135
00:06:42.033 --> 00:06:42.993
it is. Another

136
00:06:42.993 --> 00:06:48.293
principle is the notion of reciprocity of structure and function and

137
00:06:48.293 --> 00:06:49.173
all of

138
00:06:49.173 --> 00:06:54.333
these principles is that the body, you have to take all of this into account and

139
00:06:54.333 --> 00:06:55.913
therefore become aware

140
00:06:55.913 --> 00:07:00.913
that I can use that.

141
00:07:01.085 --> 00:07:01.905
It's really practical.

142
00:07:02.985 --> 00:07:03.945
That it has this power.

143
00:07:04.105 --> 00:07:05.005
And what does it ask for?

144
00:07:05.005 --> 00:07:07.485
It's simply that it be adjusted.

145
00:07:07.705 --> 00:07:10.025
There are doctors who specialize in little fingers.

146
00:07:11.545 --> 00:07:12.545
It's great.

147
00:07:12.685 --> 00:07:16.305
At the same time, they don't see that the lower limb, for example, or upper,

148
00:07:16.525 --> 00:07:18.545
is an expansion of a peritoneal sac.

149
00:07:19.645 --> 00:07:21.945
Atoms will form molecules.

150
00:07:22.505 --> 00:07:24.625
Molecules will form cells.

151
00:07:25.185 --> 00:07:26.825
Cells form tissues.

152
00:07:26.945 --> 00:07:28.545
Tissues form organs.

153
00:07:29.897 --> 00:07:35.537
So, ultimately, I am a kind of package

154
00:07:35.537 --> 00:07:36.757
of atoms moving in front of you.

155
00:07:37.937 --> 00:07:40.217
And before the atom, there is also this whole notion of energy.

156
00:07:40.377 --> 00:07:43.017
So, ultimately, what we perceive is a set of energies.

157
00:07:43.497 --> 00:07:48.037
It's a package of energy that sometimes needs to be a bit structural.

158
00:07:48.217 --> 00:07:49.137
Which thinks, moreover.

159
00:07:50.677 --> 00:07:51.397
Onto, Genesis.

160
00:07:51.917 --> 00:07:54.417
Onto, that means being.

161
00:07:55.037 --> 00:07:56.817
And Genesis, that means formation.

162
00:07:57.230 --> 00:08:00.490
Ontogenesis is the formation of a being.

163
00:08:01.770 --> 00:08:05.630
We will study the ontogenesis of man.

164
00:08:06.670 --> 00:08:09.270
And especially in its morphogenesis.

165
00:08:09.630 --> 00:08:15.010
So in its morph, in its form, and

166
00:08:15.010 --> 00:08:16.910
the formation of this form.

167
00:08:18.250 --> 00:08:19.590
An individual.

168
00:08:19.990 --> 00:08:24.790
Phylogenesis, that covers the history of the development of all species.

169
00:08:25.302 --> 00:08:30.562
through time. We will study human ontogenesis. We will especially

170
00:08:30.562 --> 00:08:31.762
look for the form

171
00:08:31.762 --> 00:08:36.562
and this power of human development and see the impacts we can have

172
00:08:36.562 --> 00:08:37.342
in practice.